<TITLE> Thai king's condition 'good', recovery needed: palace </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BANGKOK Oct 14, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Thai King Bhumibol Adulyadej's condition is "good" but he needs time to recover from pneumonia, the palace said on Wednesday after concerns over his health sparked a tumble in Thailand's financial markets. "His majesty the king's general condition is good," said a statement from the Bureau of the Royal Household. "However, a further period of recovery of lung pneumonia is necessary, as in the case of the elderly." King Bhumibol, the world's longest-reigning monarch at age 81, has been hospitalised since Sept. 19, his longest period of treatment since suffering a blood clot in 2007. The king, Thailand's single unifying figure, is regarded as semi-divine by many of the country's 63 million people. His health is an extremely sensitive topic. Thai stock prices and the local baht currency fell sharply on Wednesday on concerns over his condit
